	   <tr><td colspan=2>Another option to the Sarnak Enforcer is to just buy a plain old Staff from the monk guild, until you can find that Enforcer on auction (yes, they can be hard to come by).&nbsp;&nbsp;Decent combination of stats and weight (5/28, 6.5), and only run around 5PP if I remember right.  They won't hit magic creatures, but neither will FS, and it's only an issue for a few creatures you're likely to run into anyway (ghouls, wisps).  Heck, I trained 1HB with a staff until I finally found an Enforcer at around level 20.<br><br>Price deflation is a constant thing in the world of EQ -- while the prices on EQprices or here at Alla's are a decent starting point, most times the actual in-game prices are less (sometimes by a LOT).  It all depends on demand for the item vs. how many of that item are floating around, and the longer an item has been in existence, the more of them that will be available.  Prices also vary from server to server, typically based on maturity of server.  On T-P, the price you got on the Drolvarg/LJ Vest combo would be good, but not a huge steal.  And yes, I still wear the Drolvarg mantle also.<br>&nbsp;<br>Osano<br>Level 44 Human Monk<br>Tholuxe-Paells</td></tr>
