	   <a name=99348602119037></a>
	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f99348602119037><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=3&mid=99348602119037>RE: What is Sneak ?</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=3&mid=99348602119037#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=39551><span id=Guru>Osano</span></a>, <span id=Guru>Guru</span><br><span id=notbold>171 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Mon, Jun 25th 12:20 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[5.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Sneak is a useful thing to have.&nbsp;&nbsp;You do have to train it, but it goes up quickly, so don't bother putting more than the initial training point into it.  When you try to sneak (hit the sneak button), you may or may not be successful (at mastery, you will always be successful) -- if you are successful, the sneak button will remain greyed out and your character will move more slowly.  If you are unsuccessful, the ability to sneak will refresh shortly, and you can try again.  There is no way to tell through text whether you were successful or not.  Sneak is on the standard (5*lvl+5) level-cap formula, and permanently caps at 113.<br><br>To train, just keep mashing the button.  If sneak works, just click on the darkened sneak button to stop sneaking.<br><br>Sneak has the function of (1) reducing a Mob's aggro radius significantly, especially if you are behind the Mob, and (2) changing a Mob's /con to indifferent if it can't 'see' you.<br><br>Uses for sneak:<br><br>* Get your status with a vendor up to indifferent.  This means that a vendor that is normally 'dubious' will now trade with you.  If the vendor is 'apprehesive' normally, you can now get better prices by sneaking.  Just remember to be behind (or enough to the side) of the vendor.  If in doubt, just check the /con of the vendor and make sure it's now indifferent.  This also works with Quest NPCs that need an indifferent faction to deal with you.<br><br>* Getting by scary Mobs.  If you can get behind the Mob, but don't have a lot of room to pass, sneak by.  If you are bandaging or sitting and healing, do so while sneaking.  It greatly reduces the chances of a wandering Mob aggroing on you.<br><br>* Sneak pulling.  If two Mobs are close together, they can sometimes be split WITHOUT FD, by sneaking and moving into the reduced aggro radius of one Mob.  The reduced aggro radius of the 2nd Mob will cause it not to be aggrod when the first 'sees' you.  Sneak away until you are out of normal aggro radius of the 2nd Mob, then turn sneak off and hurry back to group with your 'single'.  Nice trick.<br>&nbsp;<br>Osano<br>Level 44 Human Monk<br>Tholuxe-Paells</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
	   <span style='font-weight: normal; font-size: 9px;'>[<a href=#top>Top</a>]</span></tr>
