	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f99351633619949><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=3&mid=99351633619949>RE: Instill Doubt - oops</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=3&mid=99351633619949#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=39551><span id=Guru>Osano</span></a>, <span id=Guru>Guru</span><br><span id=notbold>171 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Mon, Jun 25th 8:45 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[4.43]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Using ID on some of the slower MOBs is OK, even if not snared -- also, note that the lower on health a MOB is, the slower they will run when feared.&nbsp;&nbsp;When soloing outdoors, sometimes I will only use ID in the second half of the battle, to try to save myself a little damage and reduce downtime.  As Keye noted, however, this skill is NOT for dungeons and is called 'Instill Train' there.<br><br>Gratz on 46 Keye -- how's the Raster hunt going?<br>&nbsp;<br>Osano<br>Level 44 Human Monk<br>Tholuxe-Paells</td></tr>
