	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Mon, Jun 25th 12:04 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[4.43]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>I don't think you'll be able to use the skill until you're 18 again, but give it a shot, as I'm not positive.<br><br>The reason that the guard and merchants came back is because they're level 35+ -- they don't mem-wipe with FD as reliably as MOBs under level 35.&nbsp;&nbsp;And all it takes is for ONE of them to remember, and he'll re-aggro the rest.  You won't have this problem with MOBs that you'll actually be TRYING to fight at this point, as they'll all be under level 35 and will mem-wipe if you get an FD off.<br><br>ID can go up if the MOB is ANYWHERE in the zone.  I used to get a target as I zoned in as I was running somewhere and keep the target all the way across the zone (unless someone killed it, of course).  If you're just standing around training, make sure you're out of normal attack range from whatever NPC you're practicing on.  It doesn't have to be halfway across the zone, just far enough away so that if the skill WORKS, the NPC won't sense that it's being attacked.<br>&nbsp;<br>Osano<br>Level 44 Human Monk<br>Tholuxe-Paells</td></tr>
