	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f99325191940403><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=3&mid=99325191940403>RE: FD</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=3&mid=99325191940403#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=39551><span id=Guru>Osano</span></a>, <span id=Guru>Guru</span><br><span id=notbold>171 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Fri, Jun 22nd 7:18 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[4.20]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>FD will sometimes fail without a message -- this is actually well known to higher level monks and will happen more as you go higher and want to manage aggro more.&nbsp;&nbsp;This can even happen solo (it has to me), but most frequently happens in group situation where the MOB has more than just you on the hate list.  This is why it rarely happens when you are FD pulling for a group -- you're the only one on the hate list at that point.<br><br>The streak you had sounds extreme, but not unheard of.  A petition will get you nowhere in that spot, and it's definitely not the guide.  Most guides are nice people and do what they can, but they pretty much get the mushroom treatment (keep them in the dark and feed them manure) from Verant.  Verant, I don't believe, has never actually acknowledged that this IS a bug -- and yes, they've been well informed about it.<br><br>There *are* strategies for dealing with this.  For a whole hell of a lot of info on this subject, see:<br><br><a href="http://pub38.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm1.showMessage?topicID=11044.topic" target=_new>http://pub38.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm1.showMessage?topicID=11044.topic</a><br><br>&nbsp;<br>Osano<br>Level 44 Human Monk<br>Tholuxe-Paells</td></tr>
