	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Fri, Jun 22nd 12:41 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[4.61]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Conventional wisdom seems to be that ID needs to be trained up to 40 so that you don't go berzerk from frustration in practicing it.&nbsp;&nbsp;So, with that in mind, you'll need to save 22 points for ID when you get it next level.  Allowing for the 5 you get when you ding next, that leaves you with 48 points available for FD or other things.  I don't know how much it'll cost you to train FD up past the first few levels, and I don't recall how fast or slow money came to me at your level.  I'd say burn a bunch of points on FD, get it to 40 or 50 (depending on what it costs of course) - the time you'd spend training it up from nothing can be better used fighting and getting xp and making money, and it'll save your ass a million times.<br><br>As for whether you should shoot the moon on your skill points?  You want to have a good number of points available at 30 when you get Flying Kick.  It's a rokking attack, and you'll want to get it off to a good start.  Other than that I don't think there are skills you need to burn more than a point on from here on out - unless you've let something fundamental lag (like I did with 2HB).  Your Mend maxed?  You're close to where it'll always work (skill 100) - that's the only one I can think of burning additional points on.<br><br>Keyeluke <br>Monk of the Silent Fist, 45th Circle <br>Strange Brew <br>Druzzil Ro<br><br>&nbsp;<br>Keyeluke<br>Member of Tenacity - Druzzil Ro<br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=27415" target=_new>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=27415</a></td></tr>
