	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[4.60]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Well..........<br><br>You really have to figure in delay into your comparison, and you can't do that merely by observing your hits.&nbsp;&nbsp;<br><br>According to the Monkly-business.com tables, your damage output with your weapon at your level is 7.86.  A Fighting baton/cane of tranquil combo generates 7.91 at the same level, so for all intents and purposes your 2HB and a good 1HB combo generate the same damage output.<br><br>Now the balance of the story.  Your staff weighs 3 lbs more than the FB/CoT combo, so that'll impact your AC if you're over your limit.  At mid levels, if memory serves, 1 stone = about 4 AC, so you can lose as much as 12 AC in the process.  But, working to your advantage is the long delay of the 2HB - generates much less taunt, so you'll not aggro the mobs nearly as much.  Great if you've a tank in the group - easier for the bottomless hit point pits to keep the mobs on them.  But, if you're the main tank, you'll have more trouble turning the mobs from the healers and nukers.  And, lastly, I tend to be biased towards faster weapons at those levels because of the greater chance to interrupt casters.<br><br>So, at your level, the choice boils down to your fighting preferences - do you group or solo?  Do you find other tanks to group with?  Do you like to be the main tank?  etc.  Be aware that your staff will lose ground to the FB/CoT combo as you go up in level, just so you know.  At 40, you'll be doing 9.98/sec, and the FB/CoT will be at 11.3.<br><br>Note that the best 2HB that monks can use is the Runed Fighter's Staff, which at 19/20 will do less damage per hit than the big clubs, but will out-damage them all over the course of a melee.<br><br>Keyeluke <br>Monk of the Silent Fist, 45th Circle <br>Strange Brew <br>Druzzil Ro <br>&nbsp;<br>Keyeluke<br>Member of Tenacity - Druzzil Ro<br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=27415" target=_new>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=27415</a></td></tr>
